The paper deals with the development of a simplified channel model for investigating user mobility in 5G networks. The paper focuses on the propagation channel and its characteristics, which are important in the design and evaluation of wireless networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the coherence time and path diversity, which are related to information theory and signal processing, respectively. Hence, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.MM (Multimedia) are also likely categories. The paper proposes a simplified model that can be used in system-level simulations, which involves the analysis of system-level performance and optimization. Therefore, cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with the interference caused by multi-path beamforming, which is related to communication systems and protocols. Hence, cs.COM (Computers and Society) is also a possible category.
